Description: Rim and handle fragment of East Greek pottery deep plate or dish, ribbed on top of rim; part of perhaps lug handle attached to rim; glaze fired mostly orange; exterior: underside of rim glazed, one band preserved on wall; top of rim and interior slipped; top and outside of lug glazed; band of simple verticals on top of rim; top of wall inside glazed, reserved below.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.65)
